.TH "amdgpu_gem_va_update_vm" 9 "amdgpu_gem_va_update_vm" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
amdgpu_gem_va_update_vm \- update the bo_va in its VM
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" amdgpu_gem_va_update_vm
.BI "(struct amdgpu_device *adev "  ","
.BI "struct amdgpu_vm *vm "  ","
.BI "struct amdgpu_bo_va *bo_va "  ","
.BI "uint32_t operation "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adev" 12
amdgpu_device pointer
.IP "vm" 12
vm to update
.IP "bo_va" 12
bo_va to update
.IP "operation" 12
map, unmap or clear
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Update the bo_va directly after setting its address. Errors are not
vital here, so they are not reported back to userspace.
